
<div class="page-header">
  <h1>Capsules</h1>
</div>

<div class="panel panel-success">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h3 class="panel-title">List of Learning Capsules</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <p>The following capsules are currently defined in Dakshina. A Capsule represents the smallest learning unit in Dakshina
       which a student can complete. A Capsule has Study material, Assignment Details and Evaluator Instructions associated
       with it. You can then define Tracks (or Learning Paths) by choosing appropriate Capsules.</p>
  </div>


  <table class="table table-striped ">
    <tr>
      <th>Title</th>
      <th>Description</th>
      <th></th>
    </tr>

    <% @capsules.each do |capsule| %>
        <tr>
          <td><%= capsule.title %></td>
          <td><%= capsule.description %></td>
          <td>
            <%= link_to 'Show Details', capsule, :class=> "btn btn-primary" %>
            <%= link_to 'Edit', edit_capsule_path(capsule) , :class=> "btn btn-warning" %>
            <%= link_to 'Delete', capsule_path(capsule),
                        method: :delete, data: { confirm: 'Are you sure?' }, :class=> "btn btn-danger" %>
          </td>
        </tr>
    <% end %>
  </table>

</div>

<div align="center">
  <%= link_to "< Home", welcome_index_path, :class=> "btn btn-primary" %>
  <%= link_to "+ New Capsule", new_capsule_path, :class=> "btn btn-primary" %>
</div>




